text: I ordered 2 Saba sets and it was obviously overcooked. I asked the counter staff to replace another set but the chef (china lady) refused to redo. The saba is dry and tough, and the kimchi soup is tasteless. This is the worst dining experience in Elias outlet.
Food is ok and the cashier (older chinese aunty) is super unfriendly. Won’t give them more business, even if the food is alright

I ate there yesterday. The ingredients were not fresh and sour. I sent the food over, but the waiter had a bad attitude and contradicted me. I didn’t ask for a refund, but you should pay attention to it. Why use the food if you can’t eat it? , I haven’t eaten your food once, so I can taste it.
